File: The suspects are due in court on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - Two suspects have been arrested for the murder of a five-year-old Cape Town boy. The suspects are set to appear in court on Friday. READ: Poorer Cape communities 'easy target for gangs' The two suspects, aged 24 and 29, are also being held for the attempted murder of a 22-year-old man. Valentino Grootetjie died after being shot in the head in his parents’ Lavender Hill yard. Police say Grootetjie was killed when warring parties fired shots around the Drury Court block of flats. His family believe he was targeted after shots were fired through their backyard. Western Cape police say detectives worked tirelessly to track down the suspects. Last weekend civil society organisations took to the streets in protest against the violence on the Cape Flats.